I"D<h2 id="couch-surfing-airbnb">Couch Surfing (Airbnb)</h2>

<p>Traveling somewhere but don’t feel like getting a hotel room? Let’s create a
platform that allows you to find couches in the area that you can book, or post
your couch for someone else to crash on.</p>

<h3 id="specific-requirements">Specific Requirements</h3>

<ul>
  <li>User roles should include: guest, traveler, host, admin.</li>
  <li>Travelers and hosts should be able to publicly post profiles describing themselves.</li>
  <li>Hosts should be able to publicly post information about room they have available.</li>
  <li>Both travelers and hosts should be able to message each other to discuss a reservation.</li>
  <li>Once a reservation is confirmed, it should no longer be listed as available for those dates.</li>
  <li>Travelers and hosts should be able to see all reservations they’ve applied for (with differentiation for those confirmed).</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="possible-extensions">Possible Extensions</h3>

<ul>
  <li>Users can “vouch” for each other, upping their credibility across the site.</li>
</ul>
